---
import { Image } from 'astro:assets';
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import portrait from '../assets/portrait.jpeg';
---

<Base
  title="About — Arda Başarıcı"
  description="Mathematics → game development → Data, ML, and AI. Building a portfolio in public."
>
  <article>
    <div class="head">
      <div>
        <h1>About</h1>
        <p class="lede">I enjoy moving between concrete problems and the abstractions that connect them.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="portrait">
        <Image src={portrait} alt="Arda Başarıcı" width={195} densities={[1.5, 2]} quality={85} />
      </div>
    </div>

    <p>
      What interests me most isn't just finding an answer, but understanding the structure
      underneath it: what assumptions it depends on, what information it preserves, and whether
      the conclusions are actually justified by the evidence.
    </p>

    <p>
      That curiosity has taken me from mathematics to software development, and more recently
      into data, machine learning, simulation, and AI systems.
    </p>

    <h2>The path</h2>

    <p>
      I studied mathematics at Boğaziçi University — a B.Sc. followed by graduate coursework —
      and worked as a teaching assistant, leading problem-solving sessions across seven
      undergraduate courses. Over the following years I worked as a developer in the gaming
      industry, building and shipping 20+ production games and interactive experiences while
      learning how to turn ideas into working systems under real-world constraints.
    </p>

    <h2>Now</h2>

    <p>
      Today I'm exploring Data, ML, and AI through a growing portfolio of projects, reports,
      and experiments. My work often starts with a specific question and gradually expands into
      something broader: understanding decision systems, investigating model behavior, examining
      uncertainty, or looking for the underlying patterns that connect seemingly different
      problems.
    </p>

    <p>
      I enjoy building models, simulations, and analytical tools, then digging into the results
      to understand not only what happened, but why. Along the way I document the process
      publicly, including the mistakes, dead ends, and lessons learned.
    </p>

    <h2>Current areas of focus</h2>

    <ul>
      <li>Data analysis and statistical reasoning</li>
      <li>Machine learning and reinforcement learning</li>
      <li>Simulation and decision systems</li>
      <li>Experiment design and evaluation</li>
      <li>AI-assisted software development</li>
    </ul>

    <p>
      I'm building this journey in public — through <a class="qlink fwd" href="/projects/">projects
      and technical reports</a> here, and posts on
      <a class="qlink" href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/ardabasarici">LinkedIn</a>.
    </p>

  </article>
</Base>

<style>
  .head {
    display: flex;
    gap: 40px;
    align-items: flex-start;
    justify-content: flex-start;
  }
  .head > div:first-child {
    flex: 0 1 auto;
  }
  .portrait {
    flex: 0 0 195px;
    height: 195px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    margin-top: -6px;
    border: 2px solid var(--border);
    box-shadow: 5px 5px 0 var(--shadow);
    overflow: hidden;
  }
  .portrait img {
    width: 100%;
    height: 100%;
    object-fit: cover;
    object-position: 50% 26%;
    display: block;
  }
  @media (max-width: 560px) {
    .head {
      flex-direction: column-reverse;
    }
    .portrait {
      flex: 0 0 auto;
      width: 120px;
      height: 120px;
    }
  }
  h2 {
    font-family: var(--serif);
    font-weight: 600;
    font-size: 23px;
    color: var(--bright);
    margin: 30px 0 10px;
  }
  .lede {
    font-family: var(--serif);
    font-style: italic;
    font-size: 21px;
    color: var(--amber);
    max-width: 32ch;
  }
  p,
  li {
    max-width: 64ch;
  }
  ul {
    padding-left: 22px;
  }
  li {
    margin-bottom: 4px;
  }
</style>
